  "text": "Job satisfaction had a positive relationship with life satisfaction, β = .18, t(141) = 2.33, p < .05, as hypothesized. This finding is consistent with those reported by [CITATION_1] in their review of 23 different empirical studies of this relationship. Furthermore, it provides additional support for the assertion by [CITATION_2] and others (e.g., ) that life satisfaction for some workers may be partially the result of having a good job.",
